OF US SPENDING NORMAL
TIME TOGETHER

00:16.041 --> 00:18.291
WAS TO ACTUALLY TALK AND
GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER.

00:18.291 --> 00:20.250
AND THEN
CAN WE HAVE SEX?

00:20.250 --> 00:22.708
I'M NOT RULING THAT OUT,
I'M JUST--

00:22.708 --> 00:24.000
YOU KNOW...

00:24.000 --> 00:25.125
FIRST THINGS FIRST.

00:25.125 --> 00:26.750
MOVIE NIGHT WE'RE
SUPPOSED TO WATCH MOVIES.

00:26.750 --> 00:28.291
I PREFER TV.

00:28.291 --> 00:29.708
YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING.

00:29.708 --> 00:33.166
ACTUALLY, NO.

00:33.166 --> 00:35.000
BUT...MOVIES
ARE AN ART FORM.

00:35.000 --> 00:37.750
THIS IS JUST THE PABULUM
THEY STICK BETWEEN
BEER COMMERCIALS.

00:37.750 --> 00:39.166
DON'T BE SUCH A SNOB,
DAWSON.

00:39.166 --> 00:40.667
I MEAN, A TV SHOW
IS JUST LIKE A MOVIE

00:40.667 --> 00:43.041
EXCEPT SHORTER...

00:43.041 --> 00:44.500
WITH BUILT-IN
BATHROOM BREAKS,

00:44.500 --> 00:46.708
AND YOU GET
A NEW SEQUEL EVERY WEEK.

00:46.708 --> 00:48.000
SEQUELS I HATE
ON PRINCIPLE.

00:48.000 --> 00:51.333
SUIT YOURSELF.
I'M HOOKED.

00:51.333 --> 00:53.375
WHEN YOU READ MY PAPER,
HOW BAD WAS IT?

00:53.375 --> 00:54.583
IT WASN'T BAD.

00:54.583 --> 00:56.667
OH...

00:56.667 --> 00:57.708
ALL RIGHT,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:57.708 --> 00:59.834
TAKE FELICITY,
FOR EXAMPLE.

00:59.834 --> 01:01.917
AW, COME ON,
IF YOU'VE SEEN ONE HOUR

01:01.917 --> 01:04.041
OF WHINY,
OVERANALYTICAL TEEN ANGST,
YOU'VE SEEN THEM ALL.

01:04.041 --> 01:05.250
DON'T GET ME WRONG.
SHE'S PRETTY,

01:05.250 --> 01:06.959
BUT WHAT KIND
OF A HEROINE IS SHE?

01:06.959 --> 01:08.458
WELL, SHE'S--
SHE'S INDECISIVE.

01:08.458 --> 01:11.917
SHE'S BASICALLY...PARALYZED
BY SOME ROMANTIC NOTION

01:11.917 --> 01:13.041
OF THE WAY THINGS
ARE SUPPOSED TO BE.

01:13.041 --> 01:14.667
IF YOU ASK ME,
SHE'S KIND OF CHATTY.

01:14.667 --> 01:17.250
SHE'S YOU.

01:17.250 --> 01:18.208
EXCUSE ME?

01:18.208 --> 01:20.250
SHE'S YOU, DAWSON.

01:20.250 --> 01:20.834
EXCEPT SHE'S IN COLLEGE

01:20.834 --> 01:23.375
AND A GIRL AND...

01:23.375 --> 01:25.417
A FICTIONAL CHARACTER
ON A TELEVISION SHOW.

01:25.417 --> 01:27.333
EXACTLY.
THINK ABOUT IT.

01:27.333 --> 01:29.959
YOU'RE STRAIGHT OUT
OF CENTRAL CASTING.

01:29.959 --> 01:33.333
PERFECT HAIR,
PERFECT SKIN--

01:33.333 --> 01:34.583
OUR HERO.

01:34.583 --> 01:37.291
WELL,
OBVIOUSLY YOU WEREN'T
WATCHING LAST SEASON.

01:37.291 --> 01:38.750
IT WAS FAR FROM PERFECT.

01:38.750 --> 01:42.500
YOU KNOW, WHICH IS,
IN GENERAL, MY COMPLAINT
ABOUT TELEVISION.

01:42.500 --> 01:43.917
IT'S NOT REALITY,
IT'S PERFECTION.

01:43.917 --> 01:48.542
I MEAN, NOBODY EVER
BLOWS IT OR GETS TESTED
IN ANY REAL WAY

01:48.542 --> 01:53.834
OR EVER MAKES
THE WRONG CHOICE
OR BAD CHOICE OR...

01:56.750 --> 01:57.708
[TELEVISION TURNS OFF]

01:57.708 --> 01:59.708
DON'T YOU KNOW
THAT'S WHERE I COME IN?

01:59.708 --> 02:02.834
YOU KNOW, SECOND SEASON,
SHAKE THINGS UP.

02:02.834 --> 02:04.750
SCREW THE STATUS QUO.

02:04.750 --> 02:08.708
AH, A TEMPTRESS...

02:08.708 --> 02:11.458
WHO WILL TEST OUR
HERO'S VERY MORAL FIBER.

02:11.458 --> 02:14.542
WILL HE SURVIVE UNSCATHED?

02:14.542 --> 02:16.959
STAY TUNED.

02:16.959 --> 02:19.708
YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
I HATE ABOUT TELEVISION?

02:19.708 --> 02:21.291
THEY ALWAYS
CUT TO COMMERCIAL
AT THE BEST PART.

03:08.834 --> 03:12.834
[RINGING]

03:16.834 --> 03:18.834
[RINGING STOPS]

03:30.542 --> 03:31.834
DAWSON.

03:31.834 --> 03:33.834
DAWSON!

03:33.834 --> 03:35.083
DAWSON!

03:35.083 --> 03:36.125
[SLAPPING GLASS]

03:36.125 --> 03:36.375
DAWSON!

03:38.166 --> 03:39.125
DAWSON!

03:39.125 --> 03:41.375
